==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sutler
<hw>Sut"ler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>zoetelaar</ets>, OD. <ets>soetelaar</ets>, a small trader,
especially in camps, fr. <ets>soetelen</ets> to undertake low offices;
cf. G. <ets>sudeln</ets> to do dirty work, to sully, soil, E.
<ets>suds</ets>.]</ety> <def>A person who follows an army, and sells to
the troops provisions, liquors, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sutlership</ent>⟦br⟧
